text: Prince Napoléon is a title of the House of Bonaparte, an imperial and royal European dynasty founded in 1804 . Prince Napoléon may also refer to: * Victor, Prince Napoléon (1862–1926), pretender to the Imperial Throne of France * Louis, Prince Napoléon (1914–1997), pretender to the Imperial Throne of France * Charles, Prince Napoléon (born 1950) * Jean-Christophe, Prince Napoléon (born 1986)
title: Prince Napoléon (disambiguation)
